Tell HN: Dupe detection is broken for federialregister.gov
text:
(Sorry dang, not sure if you're awake yet!)

It's impossible to submit links such as https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2022/08/22/2022-17752/trade-regulation-rule-on-commercial-surveillance-and-data-security because the FTC has a blocker that breaks HN's dupe detection. I'd like to start a discussion around this particular issue, which I think is very relevant to the community here, but there's no way to submit the link without it being [dupe]'d.

Ask HN: Guys/Girls in startups, how do you manage production incident?
text:
How do you handle production incidents? Do you have a process or tool you use to mitigate and resolve them as fast as you can? Or kept things simple and you're just calling everyone to drop in the same room and start working on it?

I'm wondering at what point it becomes essential for a company to give a bit of thought to incident management and start investing in a process or a solution for this.
